OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779833501
OL,3,CLegendary jazz saxophonist Sonny
OL,4,CRollins dies aged 95
OL,6,FA statement from his publicist
OL,7,Fdescribed him as "one of the most
OL,8,Fhonoured and influential figures in
OL,9,FAmerican music of the 20th century and
OL,10,Fbeyond".
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FRollins began his career as a teen
OL,18,Fphenomenon, and was one of the last
OL,19,Fliving greats of the bebop era,
OL,20,Fworking with artists like Charlie
OL,21,FParker, Miles Davis and John Coltrane.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
