PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779833501
OL,3,CLegendary jazz saxophonist Sonny
OL,4,CRollins dies aged 95
OL,6,FHe won a Grammy award in 2002 for best
OL,7,Fjazz instrumental album with his work
OL,8,FThis is What I Do, and again in 2006
OL,9,Ffor best jazz instrumental solo for
OL,10,FWhy Was I Born?
OL,12,FRock fans could also hear him on the
OL,13,FRolling Stones' 1981 album "Tattoo
OL,14,FYou," which features a sax solo from
OL,15,FRollins on the ballad "Waiting on a
OL,16,FFriend," devised after watching Mick
OL,17,FJagger dance.
OL,26,@uD@\OUvD@EO]wD@WOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
